FBIS4-13927 "drnes079_n_94013" FBIS-NES-94-079 Daily Report 23 Apr 1994 LEBANON Israeli Shelling, Resistance Attacks in South Reported Israeli Shelling, Resistance Attacks in South Reported Shelling Injures, Kills Pregnant Women NC2304053394 Beirut Radio Lebanon in Arabic 0430 GMT 23 Apr 94 NC2304053394 Beirut Radio Lebanon Arabic BFN [Text] The treacherous Israeli shelling of Frun has caused a major massacre. Three pregnant women -- Fatimah Hamdun, Muna Hayik, and Dalal Hayik -- were injured. Dalal Hayik died while undergoing surgery and was buried yesterday with her husband Hasan Ahmad Hayik, who was also martyred in the shelling. The two other injured women were evacuated to the American University of Beirut Hospital where the leg of Muna Hayik was amputated. The twins she was carrying died. Fatimah Hamdun's fetus also died. Meanwhile, the Israeli attacks on the liberated areas continued. The hills of 'Arab Salim came under artillery shelling from the occupation forces' positions on the Tallat al-Dabshah. The southern quarter of the town also came under intensive machine-gun fire.
